*THIS IS A COURTESY POST*
*THIS DOG IS NOT AT WCHS - All information we have is posted, you must contact with questions/inquiries about adoption NOT WCHS Staff*
**Owner can be reached at jamieschacher@yahoo.com

His name is Blue, he’s approx. 3 years old, about 50-60 pounds, and is a Great Pyrenees/Blue heeler mix. He does take medication (mainly in the winter) for his hip due to being run over a year ago. He also has a bad leg from tearing a tendon, but he’s able to run around and sit/lay down normally. He is a country dog for sure. I never had problems with him chasing ducks, chickens, geese, or turkeys. He wasn’t too keen on cats and took him a while to get used to my parents' dogs. He hasn’t been exposed to older children, but he’s been around my infant twin daughters and hasn’t shown any aggression towards them. Blue does seem to be a little slow mentally, but he is a great dog overall and guard dog. 

They described him as protective, loving, and energetic.

Owner will send him with his collar and his medical paperwork. They are not asking a rehoming fee. Just want to make sure he goes to a home I know he would be cared for and treated like part of the family.

animal.description: Sweet senior Adrianne was rescued from a shelter where she was likely to be euthanized. She was very scared at first and we think she was probably used for breeding. She had major hair loss and it was clear she had birthed many litters. Her owner probably couldn't use her for breeding anymore as she is 9-years-old, so they gave her up. Adrianne has blossomed in foster care with her loving foster family! She knows she is safe now and is learning to experience the good parts of life, probably for the first time! Her hair has grown back in and her body has healed beautifully. She is looking forward to spending her golden years filled with love and treats and pets.

animal.description:
Lola is a beautiful 9 month old Shepherd mix weighing in around 50 lbs. She came to us from Mexico with her mom and siblings when she was just a baby and was adopted out at around 8 weeks. Unfortunately, she was returned to us a few weeks due to unexpected family changes. She is playful, sweet and affectionate, She has been lovely with children, but at this time, we are requiring her to go to a home without children so she can get the appropriate attention/training that she needs to truly thrive.

She has some leash aggression, can be a bit unsure around some men and has proven to be quite protective of her family/home so will need a strong leader who can set the right boundaries for her from day 1. With the right amount of exercise and boundaries we know this young girl will thrive. We are offering 2-3 sessions with a trainer to ensure that she is set up for success in her new home.

An application is the first step and is required to schedule a meeting, without exception. All of our dogs are housed in private foster homes.   Please complete application below, and include any questions in the final section.  Inquiries without applications submitted will be answered as we can. Please note that we do not do out of state adoptions, and a home check and adoption fee are required.

https://fs6.formsite.com/themuttscouts/form5/index.html


Mutt Scouts is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit dog rescue dedicated to helping homeless, abused, and abandoned dogs. We are committed to providing proper socialization, training, and medical care for each animal we save, no matter the cost. 

Please visit our website for more information about our organization:
https://www.muttscouts.org/

animal.description:
Buddy and Snowy are a 4 year old bonded pair of littermates. They have been livestock guardians for llamas, alpaca, turkeys, peacocks, and guineas. Buddy and Snowy's owner had to have surgery and is having to sell her farm so she contacted us to find Buddy and Snowy a wonderful, Furever farm. 

Buddy and Snowy are sweet, gentle dogs. They take a little time to warm up to new people since their job is to guard their livestock. They may even bark at you to let you know they're doing their job. Snowy warms up the quickest and Buddy will follow suit. They will roll over for belly rubs and Snowy is insistent with her Pyr Paw! They walk very nicely on a lead and are so gentle when taking treats from your hand. Buddy does need to be fed separately from livestock as he will resource guarding his food. Buddy and Snowy will come to you neutered/spayed, up to date on vaccines, up to date on flea/tick preventatives, and microchipped. 

Applicants must have a secure and visible fence. In order for your application to be approved, you must also pass a home check and a vet check which includes having at least a two year vet history. Children in the home can be 12 years or older. Buddy and Snowy can be adopted in Missouri and surrounding states: Illinois, Iowa, Kansas, Nebraska, and Arkansas. We are able to transport Buddy and Snowy to those states. If you would like to give Buddy and Snowy their furever home, please fill out an application on our website. 

Being fostered in Holden, MO

animal.description:
Kylo. Pitbull mix. Male. 5 years old. Dogs.


Where to even begin as this dog has a past, present and future, that we can just keep writing and writing and writing about. Rough, rough start to life, Kylo was Kilo, and dropped off at the shelter by his “owner”. This action probably, in fact, saved his life. Kilo was emaciated, had severe muscle atrophy in his hind end and a protruding spine. Medically speaking, it seems he grew up in a crate half his size and was left to rot in his own feces and urine. He was a skeleton of a white dog with massive skin infections and a diminished soul.

What Kylo didn’t know is that there was an army of love ready to help transform into Kylo the Prince warrior of the underdogs. Kylo has much more story to tell but for starters what you all need to know is that he is a gifted whisperer of life. Kylo is smart. Kylo is clever. Kylo has enough charm to get to the Queen. He has enough heart to heal the world of pain. He has his own idiosyncrasies as us all. He is an individual with depth, simplicity and a desire for savvy and compassionate leadership. We know Kylo extremely well and we are extra protective of his being. He will not ever endure human failure again. So, what is he looking for? A savvy home with little stairs and a yard would be lovely. He does loves walks and adventure. He excels in the ride or die category. No kids. He’s met kids and done very well but again, we are looking for his ultimate success and kids always complicate matters. No cats or ferrets because no one really needs that (no offense). A quiet home who loves the outdoors, snuggling on the couch and is looking for a love like no other. He wouldn’t be upset if his Forever did have a confident and social female canine sister but that’s not a must. Also, walking this dog on leash is like therapy for the soul because that is what he is a SOUL DOG.

Kylo is an incredible addition to humans who understand dog, boundaries and individuality. He has more honest love to give than any other dog or human we have ever met. We personally appreciate enjoy putting in the work to gain another’s trust, we look for humans made of the same...

animal.description:
Sake. Terrier mix. Female. 43 lbs. 4 yo.

Sake recently published her first book titled, The Grass IS Greener on the Other Side. Sake was found on a hot Chicago summer day, lying on a puddle in an alley. Crooked, malnourished body, confused, exhausted mind and a complex soul. This beauty has come so far from the broken she was. Our vet thinks her body shape is from growing growing up in too small of a crate. We have done extensive physical therapy with her where she’s gained new abilities from being fit and leading a life of love. Sake loves to talk. She’s an opinionated woman who knows what she likes. She loves watching TV while lying beside you on the couch. She think she’s a personal acting coach and speaks her mind often aloud. She has many voices. She carries passion in stride. She’s spicy and sweet. She’s looking for a simple life. A quiet life. She is great in the car and has a road trip from Chicago to California under her belt. She LOVES farm life and she loves swimming. She found a new friendship with pigs and even a cat. Sake does prefer to be the only pet indoors. Out door she cares less about what others are doing because she’s busy taking all the inspiration for her next novel... it has something to do with Forever.

animal.description:
DUE TO THE OVERWHELMING RESPONSE, WE ARE NO LONGER ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS.
THANK YOU.
Annie and Daisy are both heeler-corgi mixes that were born Aug. 5, 2020. CCK purchased them from a breeder who is retiring and we were concerned for their future. The girls joined CCK at 8 weeks of age and they will soon be 12 weeks old and looking for homes of their own. Given their breeds, these will be ACTIVE dogs and smart

Here's what their foster mom has to say about them:

First of all, they are both adorable.  They are good natured, are getting really good at pottying outside, eat well, sleep through the night, and are happy, healthy puppies.  Both are growing well, although Annie is outpacing Daisy.  Annie's legs are longer and her body is longer as well.

Annie (top) remains the adventure girl.  She is curious, bright, and pretty fearless.  She LOVES to interact with the big dogs, and will seek both Keyna and Marty out for some wrestling.  She is smart enough to be submissive, but young enough to be pesky.  (She also likes to try and play with Rhoslyn, which is hysterical!)  Annie really looks like a Heeler.  Her face is square, her body is lean, and she walks like a Cowboy.  Doug and I both think she'd do really well with other dogs to play with, and she would probably thrive in a situation where she had some work to do--chickens to chase, sheep to pester, etc.  She'd be great on some land.
 
Daisy (bottom) is a bit more reserved.  She is also curious and bright, but perhaps a little less fearless.  She will also play with the big dogs, but usually does so with Annie, rather than on her own.  Daisy LOVES people and is very affectionate.  She's not a lap puppy--too much energy for that--but she does like a bit of a cuddle when she first wakes up or is ready to go down.  Daisy comes across as a really happy puppy, and is more of a clown than her sister.  She really looks like a corgi.  Her face is triangular, her body is stockier, and her little legs are so short!  Daisy would do very well with other dogs, but I see her as the Princess of her Castle.  She's going to be that loving companion who is happy being with her people, going on walks, and ruling the roost.  
 
Neither dog is shy or aggressive with people or animals.  They will happily let you pick them up, play with their feet, interrupt their eating, and take things away that they shouldn't have.  No aggression to speak of.  Again, Daisy is gentler and Annie is more assertive, so that would want to be taken into consideration. Our preference is neither of these pups will be placed in a home where there are very small children, under age 7.
 
Both girls will have all age appropriate vaccinations and records will be provided. Their adoption fees are $300 each and application may be made through the website link.  www.corgiconnection.com

animal.description:
Pepper is a 2-3 year old Anatolian girl who has led a rough life so far. She was dumped on some land with her side where she was left outside and fed randomly by the land owner. She has had multiple litters but finally someone stepped in and decided she needed a better life and here she is. After proving to be a smart cookie when getting trapped, Pepper has done a complete 180 on her personality. She was timid, scared and unsure of everything and everyone and now she's in a home environment and loving every minute of it. Pepper is sweet, loving and great with everything and everyone she has met so far. She's good with other dogs, has been around livestock and children. She rides great in the car and has even got great leash skills. Pepper will make someone a fantastic addition to their home and we are so happy to be able to give this girl a second chance.
To see the most up to date adoption status of this dog, please visit www.bigdogshugepaws.com
This is just one of hundreds of gentle giants available for adoption at BDHPI! It is best not to get your heart set on any one particular dog upfront because there is no guarantee they will still be available once you are approved or that they are even the right match for your family. Purebred puppies are only eligible for adoption to giant breed experienced homes.

animal.description:
Last Weigh-in: 59.8 lbs.

I was taking a nap early one morning in February 2019. I had found a nice chair with some wheels on it that I figured would be a good enough spot. It was in the sunshine as the sun was coming up. A lady and her foster pup were driving by on the way to the vet and spotted me and stopped to say hi. She brought me some chicken from her lunch, but I came right up to her before she gave me any. She gave me one piece, and I let her put a leash on me, and I hopped right in her car with another piece. I hardly even realized there was another dog in the car! I was just so hungry! Since becoming a Streetdog over the past few years, I have overcome heartworms, gotten healthy, learned my indoor dog manners, worked on some basic training, and even flown on a private plane two times, and it was so much fun! I have a great time playing with other dogs, but would probably fit best in a home with no cats or young children because they make me super nervous! I am a lover for sure, and get very attached to my humans! I am looking for a foster home or, even better, a forever home and would be so grateful if you would give me a chance and open your hearts!

*Behaviors not listed have yet to be tested.

animal.description:
PLEASE READ ALL THE INFORMATION IN THE DOG'S PROFILE, AS WELL AS THE INFORMATION ON OUR WEBSITE, niagaradogrescue.com , BEFORE EMAILING US WITH QUESTIONS. OUR VOLUNTEERS USE UP VALUABLE TIME ANSWERING QUESTIONS WHERE THE ANSWERS ARE READILY AVAILABLE ON THE WEBSITE. 
SINCE WE ARE ENTIRELY VOLUNTEER RUN AND RECEIVE A HIGH VOLUME OF APPLICATIONS, IT MAY TAKE AT LEAST 2-3 WEEKS BEFORE AN ADOPTION TEAM MEMBER CAN RESPOND TO YOUR APPLICATION. PLEASE BE PATIENT.
WE ARE FOSTER BASED, THEREFORE WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY.  MEET & GREETS FOR DOGS IN CANADA WILL NOT BE ARRANGED UNTIL AN ADOPTION APPLICATION IS APPROVED. THANK YOU!!!
	
Please visit our website @ https://www.niagaradogrescue.com/ or apply for adoption @ https://niagaradogrescue.com/adoption/.    If the dog is not listed on the NDR website, please put the dog's name down anyway, profile just may have not been uploaded yet
		
Name: Tammy aka Trixie
Weight: 52lbs
Age: 3.5 years
Gender: female
Breed: pug/lab mix
Color: fawn with white neck colouring

Good With Adults: yes, but needs slow and patient introductions.
Good With Kids: No Exposure
Good With Other Dogs: Can be dog selective, slow and proper intros should be followed
Good With Cats: No, no small animals
Crate Trained: Yes
Housebroken: Yes
Energy Level: 7/10. High energy when on walks but she’ll sleep for most of the day.
Can be handled/touched: Yes
Barker: Somewhat
Escape Artist: No. She is great at staying within room boundaries within the home. She does not try to escape outside without her leash/harness on.
Food Aggressive: No
Walks on Leash: Yes
Rides Well in Car: Rides well in a crate.
Needs a home with a yard: ideally as she has high energy, and likes to have her space to run around and play.
Needs Another Dog: No, should be the only dog in home.
Can live in an apartment: No

Backstory: Tammy (aka Trixie) was pulled from a high killl shelter in Georgia. She was set to be euthanized the day she was pulled. She is a really sweet girl, she loves her people and is a little dog selective. Would do best as an only dog to start out. She could be trained to gain more confidence and possibly be introduced to other dogs.

Foster comments:
As her foster, we have found Trixie to be a loving and playful dog when she is within our home and backyard. Trixie warmed up to us within the first few days of her staying with us. She is a very sweet girl and she loves and shows affection for the people that have gained her trust.

Trixie loves to smell and stalks squirrels/rabbits in our backyard. Make sure you have a well fenced in backyard or large farm with space to run and play. Trixie can become very excited when it’s time for walkies and jumps a bit because of her excitement getting into her leash/harness. She walks decently on a leash however she does pull when she catches a good scent or sight. She can become overstimulated easily and she will need some training to learn how to meet and interact with other dogs and their humans. She might be best as an only dog in your house. During the day she loves to sleep beside us while my husband and I work from home.

Trixie is a smart dog. She is properly crate trained. She goes into her crate easily with the motivation of a treat or a simple hand motion when it’s time for bed. She’s only ever barked in her crate for bed time the first night a few times. She is house broken and has never peed or pooped within our house. When she needs to go outside of scheduled walk times she becomes a little restless and that’s her signal she needs to go outside for a bathroom break.

When we first got Trixie, she did not know any commands. She is smart and now responds to “come” and “sit” in the short time we’ve had her. We’re positive she’s capable of learning more commands. Trixie does not try to steal human food, during meals she will silently beg, but after a few minutes she’ll give up and lay down.

She loves toys and will destroy them. So make sure to get the durable, long lasting ones. She loves her Kong rope toy fox (once she removed the squeakers and stuffing) and her flexible chew ball, she’ll play with these toys daily. Every couple days, she’ll get a case of the zoomies, which is adorable. So make sure to have a few toys on hand when that happens. She has some resource guarding tendencies with her toys, however, if she gets a hold of a non-toy it can easily be switched out with either a real toy or a treat.

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Harley and I’m a big, beautiful, 8 yr. old girl. Not much is known about me before coming into IEBR, I was dropped off at a shelter with eye and ear infections as well as a UTI. The good news is all of that is cleared up and the doctor says that I’m in good shape – well except for a few pounds (ok, maybe 10) I need to lose.
I LOVE PEOPLE! I love being around them, I love attention, I love soft beds and I love toys and bones to chew on! I have very good manners, I sit, stay, walk on the leash and am completely housetrained. No accidents here! 

There’s a cat in my foster home and at first I wanted to chase it, but my foster parents told me no. Now the cat comes up to me and rubs all over my face – it’s annoying but I never bark or try to get it. I also have a foster dog sister and so far we get along pretty well. We go outside and lay in the sun together and go on walks together. We still get separated when we have bones to chew on or toys to play with because we’re still getting to know each other.

I’m crate trained and go to it on my own at night and for naps. I don’t have any signs of food aggression – I wait my turn for treats and patiently wait for my foster sister to finish eating before I check and see if she left anything in her bowl. I don’t bark at the door and when someone comes in, I’m very polite. I love, love, love bananas and apples as treats.

I can be a little silly when it comes time to play, I throw my toys up in the air and try to catch them - it’s kind of funny to watch. I’m 8 so my bursts of silliness are short and then I need a nap. I’d love a home where there are plenty of comfortable spots to nap, lots of treats and people to spoil me.

If you are interested in Harley, please visit our website: www.ilenglishbulldogrescue.org, and read through our adoption criteria to see if you meet our requirements. If you do, please fill out an application to adopt.

Harley's adoption fee is: $450.00

Visit us on Facebook: Visit us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/IllinoisEnglishBulldogRescue

animal.description:
Meet Louie the bassador!   Louie came to us at the Canine Rescue after a rescue in TN struggled to find Louie his forever home.   Louie is approximately 8 years old and weighs 65 pounds.  

Louie is a sweet boy that loves to cuddle and act like a lap dog.  He is mostly lab or perhaps a Red Fox Lab.   Louie is fairly low energy but loves to run in our fenced in area and play with a deflated soccer ball.  Silly boy.

Louie enjoys napping and hanging with his peeps. He has some toy guarding and food guarding behaviors so would do best as an only dog and no children.
Louie does jump when excited and he is a big boy so he needs a dog savvy owner.

Louie has questionable history with former owners and we think he was forced in and out of a crate regularly so he is not amenable to being forced to do things.  Poor Louie wanted nothing more than to be with his people.  But, he is such a sweet fella, that he usually doesn't need to be forced to do much.  Louie would love a quiet home without children or other pets.  He would love to have a human around most of the time to spoil him.  Louie would also prefer a fenced in yard to run when he gets the urge.  

His admirers say that he is an amazing dog and deserves understanding and pampering.
Louis has been waiting a long time for his forever home. Is it with you?

Please go to our website, www.crcpa.org, and complete an application if you are interested in meeting Louie.  Local homes only please!

Meet Gerty! She’s a friendly, affectionate girl who’s quite a “looker,” too! This 5-year old, 73-pound package of love is residing with our friends at Pope Memorial Humane Society in Dover, NH. We think she deserves a special home because she’s a special girl! 

 Gerty is a smiley dog who loves car rides, toys, treats, and very leisurely walks. Her toys of choice are tennis balls and tug ropes. 

Sweet Gerty is a gentle, loyal girl who just wants a laid back family to love.  Committed adopters who will give her time and space to adjust to her new home are on top of her wish list! 

Gerty's ideal home will be with adults that enjoy the quiet life style that she enjoys, and if you're looking for a buddy to accompany you on errands, Gerty is your girl! She is the best car buddy ever! A home with a fenced yard would be lovely (just to hang out and fetch those tennis balls!) but it's not a requirement. Any children should be 14+ and dog-savvy, and she needs a home without other pets. 

Gerty has had the opportunity to spend time in the home of a shelter staff member, and she was the perfect guest. She is house trained, non-destructive, and quiet....what more could you ask for?

Applications must be submitted online: https://popememorialcvhs.org/adoption-application/. Pope Memorial Humane Society is open by appointment only at this time. animal.description:
PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Wednesday evenings, 5 - 7 PM and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

This sweet lady is 10 year old Finesse.  She’s a very special dog and we’re looking for a very special home for her.  As you can probably tell, Finesse had a horrendous case of flea dermatitis which caused her skin to be just about raw, hence the sweater.  She’s currently in a foster home and has settled in well with the resident dog and people as well.  Finesse currently weighs about 63 pounds.  The adoption fee we’re asking is a donation to PAWS and a lifetime commitment to provide for Finesse comfort and care for the rest of her days.  She deserves nothing less.  

All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

animal.description:
“Look for the bare necessities. The simple bare necessities. Forget about your worries and your strife.” I hope I am your bare necessity and help you forget about all your worries! My name is Baloo! I am a handsome, 1 year old, 53lb., Lab mix fella! I am cuddly and love meeting new people! I am a little picky with my dog friends so slow, proper introductions are needed.  I do not want to live with any children.  I am house and crate trained! I am learning manners when on the leash and know how to “sit” when asked! I would like a fenced in yard in my forever home but it is not a requirement as long as I get exercise each day! I adore the game of fetch and love to go on adventures in the car too! The bare necessities of life will come to you. I can't help but think yours is Baloo!






My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

Name: Maggie
Breed: Pitbull/Lab mix?
Age: 2 years
Adoptable in the states of MA, CT and NH


BACON BACON BACON.. Okay, I'm not picky. I will eat anything you're willing to give me because FOOD!! Unfortunately I have found myself homeless and I am looking for the PERFECT home for me to land in! I am a PEOPLE-PLEASER and willing to WORK for your attention, or the treat in your pocket ;) I am looking for an active home that will take me on long walks or even hikes! No couch potatoes shall apply!! I can be a nervous nelly so my days are best spent with structure and routine so I know what to expect! I prefer a quiet home who will reinforce and incorporate my training into my daily routine. I am crate trained and LOVE my crate which is my safe place! I currently have a Lab brother, but I'm very picky with other doggy friends so I would prefer a dog/animal free home. Kids are loud and unpredictable so I'd prefer no kids in the home! 

I am planning to go to training camp and I am currently looking for a place to land (foster or adopter!) when I get out! Do you think you are a good fit for me?


If you are interested in adopting or fostering, please fill out an application at survivortails.org or email adoptions@survivortails.org with any questions.

animal.description:
Strawberry is as sweet as her name! She is friendly and affectionate with everyone, although her exuberance for life may make her a better fit in a home without small children or anyone unsteady on their feet. Strawberry would make a great exercise buddy. Her idea of a perfect day would be to start off with a food puzzle, followed by a hike or maybe an agility lesson or splash in the kiddie pool, time to romp around in a backyard, then a training session or nosework for her dinner, and a cuddle session to finish her day. 

This smarty pants aced her C.L.A.S.S. training program so she holds attention, has leash up manners, waits at the door, comes when called, abides by loose leash walking, offers a polite greeting, waits for the food bowl, and knows 'leave it,' 'stay,' 'give' and 'take' (trades valuable objects), in addition to two tricks! She has a history of ear infections so she experiences sensitivity around her head and ears, but that doesn't prevent her from being a loving cuddlebug. Adopt Strawberry and she'll help you meet all your fitness goals!

If you are interested in meeting Strawberry go to bestfriends.org/adopt and fill out our Dog Adoption Survey and our team will reach out to you!

IN VERMONT

Meet Waverly (bonded w Paxton)! Here is Waverly and Paxton's video collage:

https://youtu.be/8bsU85Fpb5M

Waverly is 2 1/2 years old (approx. DOB 3-17-18), female, 25 lbs., vetted, is or will be spayed and micro-chipped. Paxton and Waverly were homeless strays at the shelter in NC; they have an interesting relationship where Waverly depends on Paxton for confidence and is the decision maker but isn't a confident dog. She gets fearful in new situations where she doesnt. Waverly is crate trained, potty trained, seems to show a prey drive toward yard animals (no cats please), good with her 10 year old humans, loves attention, and is highly motivated by treats and affection. her best home would be home more often than not; she is incredibly sweet and thrives on affection and attention. She would love to be on oversized lap dog for someone. Stay tuned for more information as Paxton and Waverly are a new rescues!

If you are interested in adopting Paxton and Waverly please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out her Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.description:
Lotus is sweet, cuddly and loving. She's a bit shy at first. But she does warm up quickly. Lotus is a super sweet dog, and is good with other dogs. She was rescued in Carson City and is currently in Los Angeles. She is 3 years old and 58 pounds. She is very affectionate, loving and kissy, and tries to be a lap dog. She is playful with other dogs, minds well, is fully crate trained, and loves to chew on bully sticks and antlers and horns. She is a little nervous meeting new people but will warm up nicely. She is food motivated and easy to train. 

She loves food, of course. She'll be gentle in taking treats, she just needs to be reminded to be easy. And she loves bully sticks, antlers, horns, anything tough but safe for her.

She adores toys. She has her favorites that she plays with. And then there are the others that she'll de-squeak if she can. She has toys all over the house so that she always has one. 

She loves attention. And she likes to be with everyone. But she's also independent and will entertain herself. 

She is happy with other dogs. She'll play sometimes but mostly she just likes to be near them. And she'll cuddle with other dogs too.

She takes her meds easily. She does get a bit anxious if meals are a bit late. I assume because the prednisone keeps her a constant state of hunger. But she is good about a schedule. And she's very routine. 

She is crate trained. She loves her crate. She is only in it if we're both gone. But she'll willing go crate if needed. Especially when a treat is involved. And she eats in her crate so she doesn't try to get anyone else's food or treat.

She's potty trained. Just gotta remind her to go out regularly. She will pee if startled. Gentle handling required. 

She's also becoming a good watch dog. She'll bark at noises or odd things. But she quiets when told. 

She's still nervous on leash. But I assume it's because she hasn't had enough exposure or time outside because the prednisone requires her to be quarantined in the house. She is good in the car though. 

She's specific and routine and likes her schedule. She may seem high maintenance. But she's super easy. And she's a super cool girl with tons of love to give. And totally worth it.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Forever Home Wanted! Meet Franz!!!! (Better pictures coming soon.)

Franz came to us when his family lost everything in a house fire and were not able to provide for him any longer. Franz is leash trained, crate trained, housebroken and good with all. He absolutely loves people and other dogs. Franz has an old healed pelvic (hips) injury which will limit his activity and thus he is probably not a good fit for a home with young energetic dogs or kids or a family looking for a hiking dog. But he does love easy walks, being out and about, and hanging with his people and calm dog buddies. Our orthopedic specialist says Franz's prior healed injury is best managed with medication and gentle exercise. Franz is currently in a foster home and doing great but he'd love a Forever Home to call his own. Could that home be yours? Email dogs@labradorsandfriends.org or fill out our online application at www.labradorsandfriends.org. Franz is located in Southern California.

animal.description: PORKCHOP makes us smile! Little is known of his previous life – he was found in an alleyway in Baltimore with a “wound of unknown origin”. The bite wound on his under arm has healed completely and he has completed his mandatory 4 month quarantine and is officially available for adoption. The intake veterinarian estimated that Porkchopwas approximately five years old – if this is so, he is a very young five! Porkchop is full of puppy energy! Porkchop is deaf (as white/Merle dogs often are) but his pretty blue eyes can see just fine. Porkchop is good with other dogs but needs a tolerant dog that will put up with his boisterous nature. A patient dog that will show him the ropes and be his “ears” would be ideal. Porkchop is great with people but due to his deafness we would rather not place him in a home with a toddler or small child that might accidentally startle him. We would love for his new family to take him through a basic obedience course and work on hand signals. Porkchop is a smart boy and willing to learn! Porkchop has been neutered & vaccinated and will be microchipped and heartworm tested prior to adoption. If you’re interested in adding this drop dead gorgeous boy your family, please fill out an application at www.companimals.org. Adoption $250

animal.description: IRELAND is a 1 year old pitbull mix who is found in Philadelphia tied to a pole. She is a fun loving girl who is always in motion! Ireland is currently working with our dog trainer to learn how to be Zen. She will make an excellent hiking buddy! Ireland is reactive through a fence but when nose to nose she gets along with other dogs. We are working on her socialization as well and she may be able to be in a home with a calm male dog who will give her a positive influence. Ireland loves people but is too active for young children at this time. She is a typical wiggle butt however she will also head butt and could topple a toddler. Ireland has been spayed, vaccinated, micro chipped and heartworm tested. Her new family must make a commitment to continue with her obedience classes with our trainer or yours. Adoption $250. Please fill out an application at www.companimals.org if you are the active family that Ireland is looking for.

animal.description:
One look at the face of this strong, highly active, extremely confident dude- and the name just fits- Clint Eastwood!

Clint is not as gruffly soft spoken as his namesake, quite the opposite actually. This Bloodhound/ Plott Hound mix will stay on the trail as good as his iconic human counterpart. The great thing is he does quite well on the leash (but could always use some training refreshers), so you can be his trusty sidekick on the hunt! Again, true to character, Clint is selective in his dog friends, although he is quite fond of the larger ladies.

This boy will take an owner of equal strength, energy, and confidence. When the correct match is made, it's sure be "Sudden Impact"! 

Stop by our website today, www.hillcountryspca.com to fill out an application for Clint Eastwood, he'll be sure to go over all your information to ensure you'll be the best fit for his active and adventurous lifestyle! Do you feel lucky? Well do ya.....?

animal.description:
ANDY is a happy-go-lucky guy despite the incredible ordeal he's been through. Back in May 2020 he was alone on a reservation, no one helped him. He had an infection so bad he was septic. He body was so filled with pus (infection) that the pus formed a saddle of sorts on his rump. To top it off, a car hit him and he was left there to die. He's also been blinded in one  eye :-( His story is here: https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=3563139430373997&id=111176198903688

Fast forward to a very grateful and loving guy who likes his back scratched :-) This fella loves to hang out with. He doesn't really need another dog buddy, sadly no one taught him how to play :-( He'll happily accompany you around the garden/yard, take naps in the sun....but he truly prefers being inside and wants to ensure that he will always come inside with you. 

Currently he is sleeping in a large plastic kennel/crate and cleanup in the morning is less than 5 minutes (fortunately, he's a "hard nugget" kind of pooper ;-) There are other options to explore though too -- diapers, laser accupuncture, various gadgets that strap on like a harness that basically catch poop with a poop bag.

If you have a soft heart and can be a little creative with the sphincter issue, he is a delightful affectionate dog.

His adoption fee includes his neutering, vaccine series, rabies, deworming, microchip. He has had his tail removed due to his circumstances - barely a nub there. We estimate he was born in 2015.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy.
First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application. (Please do not call or text).

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal(s). If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this.

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you.

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets.

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets if you have any.

At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we) socially distanced as much as possible and have hand sanitizer.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please.

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos etc will do :-)

Thank you!

animal.description:
***Rachel is currently located at our rescue in Georgia but also available for adoption in the New Jersey and surrounding areas.***

Rachel appeared at the home of a local resident one day fully pregnant and close to delivering her pups. After her four pups were old enough to be moved, we took them all into our rescue. Her pups were adopted pretty quickly but Rachel, who was heartworm positive at the time, had to remain with us while she regained her health and eventually treated for her heartworms. Now that she's healthy, Rachel is ready to find her new home.

Rachel is a very friendly, calm girl who really just wants a human friend that she can love and trust in. While her initial reaction towards new people is to bark at them, Rachel turns to mush quickly once she realizes you're not a threat to her or her home. She's laid back, calm (yet very playful) and enjoys just being part of whatever her people are doing. While she initially got along very well with other dogs and may be again, Rachel now seems perfectly content being the only dog. Because of her initial reaction to new people, we'd not consider a home with young children at this time.

Besides being treated for her heartworms, Rachel has also been fully vetted and kept on her monthly preventatives since coming to us. She's gotten a bit overweight in her time with us but she'll trim down once she has a home that allows for more exercise time. Rachel appears to have some housetraining experience but may need additional training.

If interested in adopting Rachel, please submit an application at socorescue.com (no need to register or login)

animal.description:
Meet Darcy
Darcy is a beautiful Labrador retriever mix. We rescued her from a high-kill shelter and put her on her Freedom Ride for Life. She arrived on October 10, 2020. 
Darcy is 2.6 years of age. She has a gorgeous black coat and is of medium size at 46 pounds. She’s fully grown and shouldn’t get bigger. Darcy is sweet and affectionate. She loves being with people and she is friendly with other dogs. We have yet to test her with kitties and will do so for potential adopters. Darcy loves to play in the yard and she walks well on a leash, hoping that you’ll take long walks with her. Darcy is trying hard to be brave, but we can see she is struggling with all the changes in her life. She’s feeling a bit uncertain. She tries so hard, but every now and again, something will frighten her and she retreats into herself hoping that someone will come for her soon.
Darcy had a hard life before coming to our shelter. She could sure use some TLC to help her thrive. If you’re looking for a young, beautiful dog, with so many of the wonderful qualities that a Labrador has, Darcy may be the one. She is going to make for a wonderful companion to that special someone. 
Call 706-865-4135 for information on additional health services provided as part of the adoption fee.  If interested in one of our puppies or dogs, please submit an application online or at the shelter. Applications can be submitted online at: https://www.charlessmithgallhumanesociety.org/page/dog-adoption-application 
Once an application is submitted online, you will receive an email saying your application has been successfully submitted.  If you don’t receive this email within 24 hours, please check to make sure all application fields were completed or please call our shelter at 706-865-4135. All adopters must complete an approval process which involves a reference check with current/recent vet and a brief home visit if located in the immediate area. We do permit out of state adoptions. Adopters MUST come to the shelter to transport their new family member home. We do not ship nor do we transport them to their new homes. Adoption policies and application procedures are detailed at the shelter website: http://smithgallhumanesociety.org/ under tab All Adoptable Animals.
Charles Smithgall Humane Society (CSHS) is a No kill shelter. Animals in our care remain safe with us until adopted. Resident animals are primarily owner relinquished and also accepted from local Animal Control. The facility usually is operating at capacity with a list of animals waiting for space to open.
Adoptions and meet and greets are being scheduled by appointment only. Please call our office, email us or complete an application and someone will be in touch just as soon as they can. 
Location: 4823 Helen Hwy., Sautee, GA 30571, Phone: 706-865-4135
Email: smithgallhumanesociety@windstream.net
Our shelter in Sautee GA is located about 3 miles south of the alpine town of Helen in northeast GA.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.All of the animals posted on our site have been temperament tested. While not all are in the immediate area, once we have processed and approved your application, we will move the dog to our adoptive area for you to meet, greet and hopefully adopt. Sometimes we will have more than one application on a dog. That does not mean it automatically goes to another family but you should be aware of the fact that until you are approved and set up for the meet/greet.. the dog could get adopted by another applicant.Teddy is one of those great dogs that moves right in and feels like he has always been a family member. A sweet, happy temperament has always been what he is about. In fact, when asked to describe him, his foster said 'Teddy is just a happy boy. Always dancing and tail wagging. He did well with 5 dogs. He has great manners. Does all his business outside!' An outstanding family dog, Teddy is ready to love you with all his heart. He has had all his shots and been vet checked. He is ready to go! This friendly, outgoing boy is going to bring you smiles every day.A note from Teddy's foster: Teddy aka Teddy Bear is... a snuggler, a cuddler, a love bug boy. His coat is soft and lush. Teddy Bear gets along with my 2 senior dogs and especially my 16+yr old lab - they play a lot. He loves to go on walks in my neighborhood and the park and is friendly with everyone he meets. He is also house broken. I have had him a little over a week and I have had no issues. He would make a wonderful addition to a furever home. Our Teddy didn't have the easiest past. A positive training program will be required to help him catch up on all that he missed and will also help him to be your best boy. Update- No cats for Teddy. He's a bit too interested. If you are interested in Teddy, please fill out an application at:
https://reachoutrescue.rescuegroups.org/forms/form?formid=4588 Or contact:
rorrcanine@gmail.com

animal.description:
Birthdate: 5/15/2016

Breed: One of a kind

Weight: 71lbs

If Santa was looking for a new member to help pull his sleigh, we would have the perfect holly, jolly addition for his team ... CHEVY!!!! This handsome fellow has the most joyful hop, skip and jump when he sees you! He literally approaches you doing the most adorable happy dance that can only make you smile when you see his little airborne leaps and wiggles!

And talk about smiles??? He has the most engaging grin, which is only matched by that BOOP-able nose and molten hazel eyes. Just like the car, our Chevy is a classic! And we're not gonna lie ... he is a world class snuggler! With this boy you will be well loved and well exercised!!!

Before you can adopt sweet Chevy, please complete an adoption application on our website at pawscrossedny.org! Once your application is approved, you will receive a link to schedule an appointment online. If you have any questions about Chevy, please email us at adoptions@pawscrossedny.org for more information. Please understand we cannot hold any pet. All adoptions are done on a first come, first adopt basis for approved applicants.

The Shelter software system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We encourage you to select your new companion by considering each dog's individual personality and pet qualities instead of relying on a breed label that is only a guess.

animal.description:
Rasta is 3 years old and weighs 65 pounds. She is a truly gorgeous dog with beautiful coloring and green eyes. She is active, but does have her calm moments (usually when indoors). She's a smart gal and knows a couple commands: sit, come, stay. She is doing well with her leash training, but can pull a bit. Rasta must be the only pet in her household and would not be a good candidate for dog parks. Rasta does not like to be startled/woken up or to suddenly have someone get in her space without warning. This scares her. Due to this, she should not be around younger children. If someone suddenly gets in her face, she will growl or snap to let you know it spooked her and that she doesn't appreciate it. She has never bitten anyone. Rasta is sweet, goofy, loyal and just wants to love and be loved. She loves to cuddle and really enjoys attention from her family. Her adoption fee is $350 and covers the cost of her spay, all core vaccines (Rabies and Distemper/Parvo), microchip and microchip registration. If you’re interested in adopting, the first step is completing an adoption application which is available on our website, Poochmatch.com, under the adoption tab. Please read the following paragraphs for additional information about our process.

If this listing is still posted, we are still accepting applications for him/her. We do not do out-of-state adoptions on highly adoptable dogs; we would only consider out-of-state adoptions for dogs that prove hard-to-place locally. We cannot hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt.

UPDATE: ADOPTION EVENTS CANCELLED DUE TO PANDEMIC AND SOCIAL DISTANCING. If you are interested in meeting any Poochmatch dog at our weekly adoption event on Saturdays at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda, CA (5521 Mirage St.) between 1-5 PM, please fill out an application from our website, poochmatch.com, and submit it no later than 11 AM on Fridays. Upon receipt AND approval, the dog you are interested in meeting will be made available to meet on a Saturday. Due to the high volume of dogs and puppies in our foster homes, it is impossible to bring them all every Saturday. The only way to ensure that the dog that you are interested in will be at the adoption event is to FILL OUT AN APPLICATION AND BE APPROVED. Otherwise, we cannot guarantee that the dog you are interested in will be at our adoption event. If you cannot make the time frame of our events, appointments can be made at another time and location solely at the discretion of the foster parent. Please understand that private appointments will be coordinated to meet the convenience of the foster parent/transporter. We cannot hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt.

All adoption fees cover the mandatory and non-negotiable spay/neuter, rabies, microchip, microchip registration, full sets of core vaccinations (rabies and 1 set of distemper/parvo for adults, 4 for puppies) and deworming. Adoption fees vary based on age, breed, size and the costs incurred on the dog's behalf by us i.e. medical, behavioral training, etc. and they range from $225-$495.


COVID-19 PROCEDURE:
In an effort to create a safe environment for our potential adopters and our staff, we have changed our protocols and procedures during these difficult times. Starting immediately, our procedures will change from what’s written on our website and other social media platforms. Our weekly adoption event at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda is temporarily cancelled due to COVID-19 and social distancing. The only way to meet one of the dogs/puppies we have available for adoption is through completion of our adoption application through our website, poochmatch.com, before 11 AM on Fridays. On Fridays when we review the applications, we will pick the best fit for each dog or puppy applied for and coordinate mutually agreeable appointment times for the applicants who are approved that week. Private appointments are currently only scheduled on Wednesday, Thursday or Saturday of each week. Masks or bandanas are mandatory; faces must be properly covered.

With the overwhelming desire of the public to adopt at this time, we have received as many as 30 applications for one dog in just one week. Working with a staff of volunteers, we are only able to reach out on Fridays to the people we have approved to adopt. If you have not heard from us by Friday, we have selected a different applicant. If you have multiple dogs/puppies that you are interested in, please indicate each dog/puppy of interest on the application at that time so we don’t rule you out for another dog/puppy available for adoption.

Please understand, we have an influx of texts, phone calls and emails that makes it impossible to get to each and every one of you. Not just for adoption interest, but also from veterinarians, people who must relinquish dogs, people who have found a stray dog in need of pick up, etc. We are currently not in need of fosters. Due to the fact that there is such a high demand, we are sticking with strict protocol to not adopt out of Southern California. We apologize for this inconvenience and difficulty to be able to get in touch with us while there is an overwhelming desire and demand to adopt at this time. We appreciate your understanding and patience as we navigate through these difficult times with every intention to keep the public and our staff safe.

animal.description:
This sweet girl deserves a loving forever home where she can be spoiled as she had such a hard life before being rescued.  She gave birth to a number of litters but will have no more.  Mama is about 5 years old and has been spayed. She was treated for heartworms and had  a dental with a number of broken teeth removed.  What was she trying to eat or escape from that caused these broken teeth?   She had a severe allergic skin infection which has been treated and her fur is growing in soft.   She is up to date on her vaccinations and has been microchipped.

Even though she has had to bear so much hardship, she is the sweetest girl. It is hard to understand how she can have such an amazing temperament.  She loves to snuggle, be scratched, rubbed and petted, and go on walks. She knows sit including sitting on her haunches.  She so wants to please.  We know she does fine with older children; cats unknown.  She is fine with calm male dogs but tends to want to be the alpha with females.  She would do fine as an only dog.

She’s a beautiful black and white bully breed maybe mixed with a hunting dog of some sort weighing in at 50 pounds. Her foster mom reports she is a keeper.   She was rescued with a young male staffie/border collie mix who has been adopted.  Was this dog, Peanut, her son?  See the photo above with the two dogs and you decide.

If you can provide a loving, forever home for this girl, you will have a loving, forever friend.  Go to www.freedomstreetrescue.org to complete an online application.  For more information, email Rhonda at rhondabarron@earthlink.net

animal.description:
This sweet girl deserves a loving forever home where she can be spoiled as she had such a hard life before being rescued.  She gave birth to a number of litters but will have no more.  Mama is about 5 years old and has been spayed. She was treated for heartworms and had  a dental with a number of broken teeth removed.  What was she trying to eat or escape from that caused these broken teeth?   She had a severe allergic skin infection which has been treated and her fur is growing in soft.   She is up to date on her vaccinations and has been microchipped.

Even though she has had to bear so much hardship, she is the sweetest girl. It is hard to understand how she can have such an amazing temperament.  She loves to snuggle, be scratched, rubbed and petted, and go on walks. She knows sit including sitting on her haunches.  She so wants to please.  We know she does fine with older children; cats unknown.  She is fine with calm male dogs but tends to want to be the alpha with females.  She would do fine as an only dog.

She’s a beautiful black and white bully breed maybe mixed with a hunting dog of some sort weighing in at 50 pounds. Her foster mom reports she is a keeper.   She was rescued with a young male staffie/border collie mix who has been adopted.  Was this dog, Peanut, her son?  See the photo above with the two dogs and you decide.

If you can provide a loving, forever home for this girl, you will have a loving, forever friend.  Go to www.freedomstreetrescue.org to complete an online application.  For more information, email Rhonda at rhondabarron@earthlink.net

animal.description:
Bella is one of our Prison Program pups.  She has been trained and knows basic obedience commands.  She has also passed her Canine Good Citizen Test!

Here is a little bit about her. 

BELLA -  Unique Bella, despite her challenges in life Bella always has a smile, you can't hold this girl down!  Bella is insecure about her deformity and does not do well with dominant dogs but if you give her time and show her that they are not going to hurt her or pick on her she would love a friend to play with.  

She loves attention and will give you inspiration to put your best foot forward daily as she does.  Bella loves to learn new skills and is extremely obedient.  She is playful and enjoys a good romp but needs time to rest between exercises.  If you are looking for a strong willed partner in crime, Bella is the one for you!

Bella is about 2 years old and she is a medium size mixed breed gal.

If she is just what you are looking for in a companion please apply to adopt Bella at: empirerescue.org.

animal.description:
Hi I am Bentli! I am a three-year-old medium sized (about 45 pounds) Pitbull-mix female. Everyone who meets me says “wow she is smaller than I expected!” I am house trained and also know how to sit and shake but would really enjoy learning some other commands. If I have my Lola collar on, then I am great at walking on a leash! My biggest fear is disappointing my foster family as I am a huge people pleaser! 

I am shy at first but once I warm up to you, you’ll learn very quickly that I’m a high energy lady that is obsessed with cuddles. I will try to be in your lap at all times. You’ll know we’ve bonded when I show you my belly to rub and when I give you sloppy kisses. There is no such thing as too many cuddles or pets for me! I am crate trained but I prefer to be with my human when possible. I would prefer to be the only dog in my forever home as I want all the love and affection focused on me. 

I can’t wait to run all over your backyard and get out my zoomies! Running around multiple times a day is the best! My favorite things to chase are birds and squirrels. It’s a fun game! Your fence should be at least 6 feet tall because I can jump like it’s no one’s business! Running also helps me get out my anxiety. I’m not sure if I am faster at running or gobbling down my breakfast/dinner. I sure love when it’s time to eat!

I also love going on car rides, so don’t hesitate to take me with you to low-key places like walks and your local home improvement store. Because I’m an active gal, I would love to go on runs with you or even go on a hike that isn’t too populated with other people and other dogs.

I love my single ladies! If there is a man in the house, you will need to be patient with me; but with time, and small doses of exposure, I will accept him. Dog-savvy kids 8 years old and up would be fine to have around, but young kids kinda scare me because of how unpredictable they are. If you are someone who has lots of friends over, or friends with other dogs or young kids, I would prefer to be in the comfort of my crate. Due to my anxiety I can be shy and a little scared and vocal at first, but I will warm up to you and your guests once I am no longer overwhelmed. Even though I’m crate trained, I can sometimes get a little chatty while in my crate, but it’s just to remind you of my presence.

So, if you’re looking for a fun-loving, active pup to be your loyal companion, then I’m the girl for you! Let’s meet! Please fill out an adoption application to see if we are a match – https://www.mustluvboxersrescue.com/adopt.

animal.description:
Perri is a 2 yr old  beagle/pointer mix that weighs 30 lbs.  She is so sweet and playful    
She is spayed, up to date on shots , heartworm negative and microchipped.   
She  is great with kids, adults and other dogs.  Loves to play.
She  walks great on a leash and does ride good in the car.  

She will need a fenced in yard, no exception. because she will run off and she loves to be outside. She has a lot of energy and would love another dog to run and play with outside.
  
Fees/Payment Options:

Adoption fee is $150


Adoption fees include: Microchip, spay/neuter, rabies vaccine, up-to-date (age appropriate) vaccinations.

Dachshund Rescue of St. Louis does NOT accept checks as a form of payment for adoptions. We require cash or the use of PayPal, debit, and credit cards.

 

Adoption Process:

Completion of an online adoption application is required to be considered for a meet and greet and/or adoption.  

Upon approval, applicants will be contacted for a phone interview.

Pending phone interview(s), a meet and greet will be arranged with the foster home.

To complete the online adoption form, go to http://www.playfull-paws.com, click on adoption application

animal.description: Meet Aria! Aria is a 4-year-old mixed breed who might have some mastiff in her. She currently weighs 61 pounds. Aria came to us when her previous owner could no longer care for her, but Aria has been having a great time since she came here. She is a very sweet dog and will make an excellent addition to any family. Aria does prefer to be the only dog in the home. If you would like to meet her, please contact us at adoptions at 505-983-4309 x 1610 or email us at adoption@sfhumanesociety.org If you have another dog at home, please bring them in for a meet n' greet. Aria's adoption fee is $130 which includes her spay surgery, a microchip, age appropriate vaccinations and 30 days of complimentary pet insurance. A licensing/microchip fee may apply. We're excited to announce that our training classes have become virtual and are facilitated through Zoom meetings. See https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/group-training-classes/ for more information about schedules and registration for online training classes. We are also offering support for recent adopters through our Trainer Talks also through Zoom meetings, prior registration is required. For schedule and registration please see https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/special-seminars-and-workshops/. To see more of Aria click on the video!

Good with men/strangers:  yes
Hypoallergenic:  no

Special home requirements or medical:  must be the only pets in the home

Additional info:

Ivy and Pippa are a bonded pair and must be adopted together. These girls are two peas in a pond and are 2 perfect little book ends.   They can get overwhelmed easily so they are looking for a quiet and calm home with no other pets as they want to be the babies in the household. Pippa adjusts pretty easily, but it does take Ivy some time to get used to new environments so she will need some time and patience in her new home. Pippa is pee pad trained, but Ivy does need to be taken out often so they need a home that has a fully enclosed patio or yard where there is easy access to take Ivy out often. They are low energy, cuddly little ladies, that are crate trained, easy going and calm.

1.       Visit www.dogswithoutborders.org

animal.description: Hi! My name is Bricks and I was rescued from a shelter in Georga. I was nervous when I first arrived at the shelter, but I'm feeling much more comfortable now! I'm very sweet and quite resilient. I love getting visitors here on the ranch and would be a great greeter at your front door! I love playing catch but I don't like to give the ball back. I am also very comfortable on leash and love to go for walks. I can be protective over my things and my home so new visitors aren't always the best. I can't imagine anything better than finding a home with a great big yard for me to release all of my energy. I would much rather have a relaxing day in with you at home, and am pretty independent. Because of this picking me up is a no no because I like to show how I'm an independent pupper. I am fairly well-trained, but I would love to learn more new skills when I join your family. A home with older kids and no small animals is best. I hope to be a part of your family!

This bonded senior pair is looking for a semi-active retirement life! They love to romp around the backyard and do zoomies on the lawn, but also like to spend most of the day lounging with their people.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Thank you for considering adopting one of CARA's Special pets! To apply read about our adoption policies
here
to fill out an application.
Hey there! Let me tell you a bit about myself. My name is Pandy aka Pandora. I am CARA's longest resident. Not sure why because I am very special. Maybe it is because of my breed. Despite being so stressed out in my kennel here, when I am lucky enough to leave my kennel and spend time with the humans here, I make the MOST of it! I will graciously sit in their lap and get all the snuggles, or sit very pretty for a treat. I LOVE food, so I will be easy to train! I have very good home manners, the only thing I need to work on is greeting new people when they come to my home (mainly new adult men, they scare me). I am housebroken. I get along with older small dogs. I also get along with laidback cats.

I would am apartment friendly. I need an owner willing to work with how I meet new people in a home. I am great in public. If you are looking for a laid back, homebody that is super duper grateful to be alive, please look no further!!!To see more animals for adoption, please visit the CARA Website

Our adoption fees are:
Dogs: $155
Cats: $95
Puppies under 4 months: $115 plus S/N Deposit: $100
Kittens under 4 months: $70 plus S/N Deposit: $100

All pets available for adoption have been spayed or neutered (unless under 4 months please read about our adoptions
here
), are current on vaccinations and preventatives, and micro-chipped. Cats have been tested and confirmed negative for Feline AIDS and Leukemia. Dogs have been tested for heartworm disease.

Our shelter is located at 42 Deep River Rd in Sanford and is open Tues, Thurs, & Fri from 3pm - 7pm & Sat from 10-2pm (other times available by appointment). CARA's adoption process and online application can be found at
http://www.cara-nc.org/info/adoption

Please call 919-774-9433, email adoptions@cara-nc.org, or visit www.cara-nc.org for information about this or other pets available for adoption.

If you would like to adopt me or any of my friends, please visit CARA to fill out an on-line application or e-mail us at adoptions@cara-nc.org.

Every animal that comes into the CARA program is here because one or more events occurred that led to this animal needing not only a home, but a person or family to love and protect them. Each animal has been loved and cared for by a small and determined group of people who want nothing more than to know each animal is safe for the rest of his or her life. Thank you for looking to adopt!

animal.description:
MEET JACK!!

To visit with this pup, please make an appointment here: https://mcaccappointments.as.me/adopt. NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show. We have been told that you can go straight to the shelter and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog. From what we understand, the shelter will squeeze you in except between 12-3PM and near the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog. We hope your adoption process is smooth and full of happiness!

This amazing pup is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4473527.

Jack was recently found as a stray and brought into the shelter by a good samaritan. He was adopted shortly after but was brought back by the adopter. Jack has some issues that need to be addressed. He can be calm and easy and walks on a leash easily. He likes treats and is okay when you pet him but there are certain parts of his body that he doesn't like petted. He doesn't like his belly petted and if Jack thinks he's going to be picked up, he immediately tells you he doesn't like that. If he's laying down and someone tries to move him, he doesn't like that either.

Jack didn't like the other small dog that was in the home so he would be better as an only dog. Also, because of his behavior and history, he cannot be around small children. Jack needs behavior training to learn his manners. He also needs a patient adopter that understands his behavior traits and what he does and doesn't like. If you can work with Jack and understand his behavior traits, come and meet him today.

This is Jack's second time back at the shelter due to his bite history. Jack ieeds an experienced owner who understands the JRT breed and can help Jack on his training. Are you interested in helping Jack and want to foster or adopt him? Call the shelter today!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4473527.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Spud is a 5 year old catahoula mix. This sweet guy came to Wags and Wiggles a few months ago after losing his family in the south. Spud comes with a strict set of training rules, has received extensive training at a local training facility, and he cannot handle a family that does not understand and commit to his leadership needs. He does not belong on a couch or human bed, a floor is where he will find comfort. Spud is affectionate but cannot handle severe affection to his face; he prefers to be pet. Only serious applicants may apply for this great gent.

A family without children and cats may apply.

*
Dogs are adopting out quickly. Please know we are following covid-19 guidelines by practicing safe social distancing and other safe measures at the time of adoption. Our dogs are only shown to approved applicants at time of adoption outside.*
As with all our dogs we will require proof of a obedience course as we feel it is very important for the new family regardless of previous dog training experience to complete a training class soon after adoption to not only establish basic obedience but to bond with your new dog as well as socialize it. Many trainers have resumed training including outdoor classes.

*
If interested in this pup please fill out an application on our website wagsnwiggles.org Please be sure all members of your family are on board with adopting a new family and you are ready to adopt NOW. A volunteer will be in touch to discuss you your application and the dog to determine if a good match. Your references, including your vet will be called. A virtual home visit done and finally a meet and greet and adoption if all are in agreement. Adopt fee is $425 for adults, $475 for dogs under 1 yr. which includes core vaccines, dewormed, current on flea/tick and heartworm preventatives, microchip, health certificate, heart worm/lyme test if over 6 months and spayed or neutered. Any questions please email wags.n.wiggles.rescue@gmail.com

animal.description:
Our handsome boy Drake is a 4 year old Rottweiler/ Doberman mixed breed! He came to us from a shelter partner in Georgia in October 2020. He has lots of energy, so tons of activity is exactly what he's looking for! He would love an active owner(s) that can take him for long walks or hikes! He is very strong so he will need training on the leash because he pulls! He can be a bit overwhelming for small children, so a home with older children (preferably over the age of 15) or just adults is preferred. He is a very smart boy that loves to learn! He knows basic commands, such as sit and stay. He loves treats and is very food motivated! He seems to have missed early socialization with dogs when he was a puppy, so he would really prefer to be your only pet! He is very loyal and loving, making him the perfect dog for someone who lives alone or wants a great companion! 


If interested in fostering or adopting Drake, please submit an online adoption application! Due to COVID-19, all animal meetings must be scheduled by appointment. After we receive and review your application, we will contact you to schedule with us! Thank you!

animal.description:
Muffin Chihuahua Mix, Female, 8 years old, 8lbs, Crate Trained / Established Potty Habits Meet Miss Muffin! In the short time she's come into her foster home, she has done a lot of work to try to get to a place of the happy little dog that lives buried in her broken heart.

She's been let down by humans in the past and isn't quick to trust. Muffin will need to go to a home with an experienced dog owner who is ready to devote the time and energy it will require to keep Muffin progressing through her anxiety. She will not do well in a home with other dogs or small children. She hasn't been tested with cats. She is very scared of a leash and collar/harness so a fence is a must if outdoor potty breaks are desired, otherwise she is good using pee pads although not 100% accurate. She does not currently potty outdoors and this will take a lot of time and secured training if ever achievable. She loves her people once she's reassured they aren't going to hurt her, but can react if startled and her anxiety takes over.

Muffin does resource guard her blankets, bedding and occasionally toys. Extra precaution needs to be addressed while she's nesting and comfortable. She does initiate cuddles on her terms and has a lot of love inside of her. Muffin can be very playful and loves her toys, she's a great sleeper and deserves a cozy spot next to her human. If you're interested in learning more about Muffin, please fill out an application and I'd be happy to talk your ear off about this quirky beautiful soul that needs a second chance.

All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations, heartworm tested negative (age 7 months and older) and microchipped. We do not ship or transport. A dog's adoption donation is $200. There is a $5 fee for credit/debit cards.

If you are interested in adopting one of our dogs, please fill out an online application here: www.heartlandsmallanimalrescue.org/canine-application.html

He will bond with his person or people and his joy in loving you and being loved by you will fill your heart and his. He’s smart and funny and gets the zoomies once in a while, so he would do great in a yard with a little room to zoom and a high fence. He also does great on car rides and loves to go on walks, but he is a big guy (75+) and is still working on basic commands and leash manners. Although he’s six years old (we think), he has the attitude and sense of adventure of a dog half his age. And when you’re ready for some downtime on the couch, he couldn’t be happier to snuggle up and join you. He only barks when he has a reason to bark, and he’s housebroken. He can be a little fearful in new environments and when he hears loud noises or is startled and might run and hide, but as long as you are patient with him at first, you will be rewarded with his full trust.
Apply today at www.realrottweilerrescue.com 

Please note: The prospective owner must agree to a screening process that includes an application and the signing of an adoption contract.

Our goal is to find the best match for our dogs and their new families, so that everyone lives happily ever after.

We prefer homes who want to go to an obedience class. Training strengthens the bond and trust that you have with your dog, and it's fun, for both of you! Dogs like to think and to be mentally challenged. The training you do together will be an investment in the future. 

We will try to respond within 24-48 hours, but please be patient as we are volunteer based. We all have full time jobs and are busy with other rescue matters.

Thank you!
